Aug 5 2009 	Great Hotel Good/Safe Location Highly Recommended for SF First Timers	This is the first time we visited San Francisco, and we're so glad to have chosen this hotel as a great introduction to the city! Japantown is not too far from the main San Francisco attractions, yet not too close to the noisy, overcrowded streets of the more popular parts of the city. It is a very safe &amp; clean place to walk around, and there are plenty of Japanese restaurants, grocery stores, and gift shops steps away from the hotel. The hotel accommodations we great - the room was very clean and looks just like the pictures from the hotel's website and the king size bed was very comfortable. On our floor it was pretty quiet - we did not hear other travelers at night, but maybe because we stayed on weekdays. We visited the main attractions using public transportation and walking. There are a couple of bus lines very close to the hotel, depending where you want to go. If you look at a map of San Francisco, you will see that Japantown is only 10-15 minutes away by bus to most major attractions. We also used our GPS to find good restaurants/shops and were delighted to find that you can get to them within a 2 mile radius. The doorman and staff were also very helpful in arranging taxi or helping you figure out which bus line to take. We would recommend first time travelers to San Francisco to get the city pass (available on SF's visitor website), which includes passes to main attractions and 7 day, unlimited pass to all the bus/muni/trolley public transportation.	
