May 12 2009 	nice hotel for the price safe location	MY boyfriend is from Texas and had been wanting to go to San Francisco for a while, so I was watching travelzoo for good prices on hotels in San Francisco. The Hotel Kabuki came up for $75/night, so I checked out reviews on tripadvisor and decided to go for it. The price seriously can't be beat in the city. We were able to park in the valet lot in front of the hotel to check in and decided not to pay the extra money for valet parking. I had read that the downstairs parking does not have in and out priveleges and that the lot closes from like 2:30-5am or something. I must say that during checkin, I did see a sign clearly posted on the counter that noted the $50 fee for checking out during those hours if using the self parking. We had to drive about half a block to get to the parking lot, however it stretched underground from Benihana to the hotel elevators, so I did not find it necessary to unpack in the valet parking because we parked right by the hotel elevator. The neighborhood seemed clean and safe, and I did not experience the issue with noise that I had read about from other people. The city can be a noisy place, I don't think it's anything the hotel could have helped in those situations. I had signed up for the loyalty club before our visit and they gave us a view upgrade which was the 13th floor. The balcony is narrow, but perfect for viewing the city. I loved the soaking tub, and we went to Lush in union square and got some bath goodies for it. I noticed that a few people had mentioned rude staff in their reviews, but we had not one bad thing to say about the staff. They seemed friendly and helpful. In fact, one of the girls at the desk spent about 10 minutes with us discussing the different types of public transportation, how much they cost and how to get there. We will definitely be going back!	
