Mar 2 2009 	Enjoyable neighborhood and comfortable hotel	We stayed at the Kabuki February 2009 for 5 days. We found the people friendly and helpful and the location great for us, as we love Japanese food, sampling the local restaurants and exploring the local markets. It's located next to the Japan Centre, full of great shops and restaurants in several buildings. We got a nice Internet Special deal, which made the price within a reasonable range. The Filmore district, with tons of jazz clubs, is only a few blocks away, and there is a bus that goes to Union Sq nearby. The Filmore farmers market (walk past the Japan Centre, make a left on Filmore and walk 2 or 3 blocks) is in a lovely outdoor venue on Saturdays with an excellent jazz band playing, a great place to spend a few hours on a pretty Saturday. (Great produce vendors where you can pick up some fruit--Don't miss the Afghani food vendor--you will want to have some of their stuffed bread and sauces for lunch). There is a Starbucks there as well...2 snags on the room: Wireless is an extra charge, and no simple breakfast options for early risers: The hotel's buffet is expensive--even what they call &quot;continental&quot; breakfast, and there is no provision for just getting coffee and a roll or something. The Japan Centre eateries don't open before 10:30, even the deli and crepe place. There is an electric kettle and cups, and a japanese teapot and cups in the room, but no coffee maker and no tea supplies--we had to buy some at the market ourselves. One day we had toast and coffee sent up to the room, and Saturday we ate pastries at the Farmer's Market &amp; got coffee at Starbucks there. We did find a kind of dodgy place a couple of blocks away finally, and had breakfast there--the only customers in the place. That cup of coffee or tea in the morning is important to us!If a visitor wants to see all the major sights, etc., maybe there are more convenient places; we are an older couple with children in the area who take us to events and the parks, though, so we really loved the neighborhood.	
